      "question": "What's the difference between early blight and late blight?",
      "intent": "comparison",
      "applicableTo": ["early_blight", "late_blight"],
      "answer": "**Early Blight (Alternaria solani):**\n- Circular spots with concentric rings\n- Starts on lower leaves\n- Brown lesions\n- More common in moderate temps (20-25째C)\n- Slower progression\n\n**Late Blight (Phytophthora infestans):**\n- Water-soaked lesions\n- White mold on leaf underside\n- Can affect entire plant rapidly\n- Prefers cool, wet conditions (15-20째C)\n- Can destroy whole crop in days\n\n**Key Difference:** Late blight is more destructive and spreads faster. It's the disease that caused the Irish Potato Famine.",
